parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes smell hot
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle vibrates or pulls to one side
the ABS light illuminates
and the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to a loss of stopping power and potentially causing accidents or injuries.

the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle vibrates or pulls to one side
and the brakes smell hot.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission misshifting can cause sudden loss of power, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The transmission shifts into the wrong gear
